BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp
 -content/uploads/2026/05/Kicking-it-at-the-Commons-Square.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://hermannpark.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/0
 5/Kicking-it-at-the-Commons-Square.jpg
UID:vaY5S9rgo2YgFGAqY1RN3
SUMMARY:Kicking It at Hermann Park
DTSTAMP:20260617T163157Z
DTSTART:20260612T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:This summer\, Hermann Park Conservancy will welcome the world t
	o Houston with Kicking It at Hermann Park\, presented by ExxonMobil—a free
	\, public celebration of culture\, community\, and the unifying spirit of 
	sport. Featuring a dynamic mix of programming\, diverse food offerings\, l
	ive entertainment\, and family-friendly activities\, everything will take 
	place in the Commons\, the vibrant 26-acre play and gathering space in the
	 southwest corner of the Park. \n\n📍 The Commons at Hermann Park\n📅 Weeken
	d and select weekdays from June 12 – July 5\n🎟️ Free & open to the public\n
	\nKicking It at Hermann Park will run on weekends and select weekdays from
	 Friday\, June 12\, through Sunday\, July 5\, offering 15 days of engaging
	 experiences for Houstonians and visitors alike during a globally signific
	ant moment for the city. \nThe roster of dynamic programming will include:
	 \n\n🎶 Live music & entertainment\n🍴 Local food trucks & culinary offering
	s\n🎬 Outdoor movie nights\n⚽ Soccer-inspired play & interactive experience
	s\n🌿 Nature-based activities\n👨‍👩‍👧 Family-friendly programming\n🎭 Cultural ce
	lebrations highlighting Houston’s diversity\n\nThank you to ExxonMobil for
	 their generous support! \n \n+++ \nDATES & THEMES\nStay tuned for more de
	tails and a complete programming calendar. Activities are subject to chang
	e and more may be added. Visit the Conservancy tent on-site in the Commons
	 for any questions!\n \nWEEKEND ONE (JUNE 12 – JUNE 14) PDF SCHEDULE HERE.
	 \nFriday\, June 12 (5 – 9 p.m.): Kickoff in the Park \n\n5 – 6 PM: Trees 
	for Texas: A Backyard Tree Walk (Astros Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)
	\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel Karaoke (Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n6 – 7 P
	M: Seeds for Success: The Art of Starting a Garden (Cullen Pavilion – The 
	Commons)\n7 – 8 PM: Perennials in the Park: Garden Discovery Tour (Astros 
	Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Decks: Live DJ Experien
	ce (Powell Foundation Terrace – between Water Play Area and Space Adventur
	e in the Commons)\n\nSaturday\, June 13 (3 – 10 p.m.): Texas Heritage \n\n
	3 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n3 – 4 PM:
	 T is for Texas! Twanda’s Theatre on Wheels from Young Audiences of Housto
	n (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Hidden Invaders: Underst
	anding Invasive Species (Next to Lott Family Carousel – The Commons)\n4 – 
	5 PM: Rhythms of Tradition: Mixteco Ballet Folklorico from Young Audiences
	 of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Winding Paths 
	of the Japanese Garden: Guided Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 PM: “One Wan”: Ja
	panese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n5 -6 PM: Perennials in the P
	ark Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n5 – 8 PM: Hooked on Fishing! Youth
	 Fishing with 4-H (Fishing Pier – The Commons)\n5 – 8 PM: DJ Areal: Music 
	in the Commons (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: A Walk Thro
	ugh Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n8:30 PM: Moonligh
	t Movie Nights presented by Goya: The Parent Trap (Doreen Stoller Lawn – T
	he Commons)\n\nSunday\, June 14 (3 – 9 p.m.): Family & Global Community Da
	y \n\n3 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n4 –
	 5 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\
	n5 PM: “One Wan”: Japanese Garden Tea Ceremony (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 6 PM
	: Mosaic Workshop from Young Audiences of Houston (Astros Foundation Pavil
	ion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Bats-a-Billion: Discover the World of Bats (
	Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Winding Paths of the Japanese Ga
	rden: Guided Tour (Japanese Garden)\n7 – 9 PM: Jazz in the Park with Bayou
	 City Jazz Band (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n\nWednesday\, June 1
	7 (3 – 9 p.m.): Wellness in the Park – THIS DATE HAS BEEN CANCELED DUE TO 
	INCLEMENT WEATHER! \nFriday\, June 19 (5 – 9 p.m.): Juneteenth Celebration
	 \n\n5 – 6 PM: Kick Into Creativity by Eco Art Studio (Astros Foundation P
	avilion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Gar
	den Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 7 PM: Carousel Karaoke (Lott Family Carous
	el – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Voices from the Past: “Git” On Board – The Li
	fe of Harriet Tubman from Young Audiences of Houston (Tsuru Family Terrace
	 – The Commons)\n6 – 7 PM: Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial Garden
	s)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Departmen
	t (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n7 – 9 PM: Open Dec
	ks: Live DJ Experience (Powell Foundation Terrace – Between Water Play Are
	a and Space Adventure in the Commons)\n\nSaturday\, June 20 (3 – 10 p.m.):
	 Global Rhythms \n\n3 – 4 PM: Trees for Texas: A Backyard Tree Walk (Astro
	s Foundation Pavilion – The Commons)\n3 – 4 PM: Sonidos Sincopados with Jo
	rge Orta from Young Audiences of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Ar
	eas in the Commons)\n3 – 6 PM: Pop-Up Performances (Miller Outdoor Theatre
	)\n4 – 5 PM: Beast Boogie (Anthony Silva) Dance Demo from Young Audiences 
	of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 -5 PM: 
	A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanese Garden)\n5 – 6 
	PM: Perennials in the Park Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n5 – 8 PM: D
	J Hiram: Music in the Commons (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the 
	Commons)\n6 – 8 PM: Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Dep
	artment (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n8:30 PM: Moo
	nlight Movie Nights presented by Goya: A Bug’s Life (Doreen Stoller Lawn –
	 The Commons)\nAll Day: Goya Giveaways (Next to the Carousel and Play Area
	s in the Commons)\n\nSunday\, June 21 (3 – 9 p.m.): Community & Wellness D
	ay \n\n3 – 4 PM: A Walk Through Tranquility: Japanese Garden Tour (Japanes
	e Garden)\n3 – 7 PM: Activities with The Health Museum (Astros Foundation 
	Pavilion – The Commons)\n4 – 5 PM: Make Your Own Mandala with Young Audien
	ces of Houston (Next to the Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n4 -5 
	PM: Origami in the Japanese Garden (Japanese Garden)\n4 – 8 PM: Kindstatio
	n by Be Kind (Cullen Pavilion – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM: Wellness Walk with
	 Urban Paths’ Laura Conely (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n5 – 6 PM:
	 Roses in Bloom Tour (McGovern Centennial Gardens)\n6 – 7 PM: Pilates in t
	he Park by Revival Pilates (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n6 – 8 PM:
	 Soccer for Success by Houston Parks and Recreation Department (Next to th
	e Carousel and Play Areas in the Commons)\n7 – 8 PM: Yoga in the Park by B
	lack Swan Yoga (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n8 – 9 PM: Prioritizin
	g Peace: Sound Bath (Tsuru Family Terrace – The Commons)\n\nTuesday\, June
	 23 (3 – 9 p.m.): Youth + Play + Sustainability Day \nFriday\, June 26 (5 
	– 9 p.m.): Latin Night \nSaturday\, June 27 (3 – 10 p.m.): Global DJ Night
	 \nSunday\, June 28 (3 – 9 p.m.): International Culture Day \nMonday\, Jun
	e 29 (3 – 9 p.m.): Arts + Nature Day \nFriday\, July 3 (5 – 10 p.m.): Summ
	er Nights in the Park \nSaturday\, July 4 (3 – 7 p.m.): Celebrate America 
	– Houston Style \nSunday\, July 5 (3 – 9 p.m.): Closing Celebration \n+++ 
	\nMOONLIGHT MOVIE NIGHTS\nPresented by Goya \n \nAs part of the summer off
	erings\, enjoy Moonlight Movie Nights\, presented by Goya\, in the Commons
	! Movies will start at approximately 8:30 p.m.\, around sunset. These movi
	es are free and open to the public. \n\nSaturday\, June 13: The Parent Tra
	p (1998\; PG)\nSaturday\, June 20: A Bug’s Life (1998\; G)\nSaturday\, Jun
	e 27: Lilo & Stitch (2002\; PG)\nFriday\, July 3: National Treasure (2004\
	; PG)\n\nBe sure to get to the Commons early to snag your spot on the lawn
	. Guests are welcome to bring blankets or lawn chairs to settle in for the
	 movie. \n+++ \nTo inquire about sponsorship opportunities and ways to get
	 involved\, email community@hermannpark.org.\n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/ev
	ent/kicking-it-at-hermann-park/\n\nFrom Hermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/kicking-it-at-hermann-park/
LOCATION:The Commons
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hermann-park
CATEGORIES:Hermann Park Conservancy
